      "date": "2016-02-12 22:51:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBob, I'm just comparing the SLES12 and RHEL7/7.2 patches and am wondering if the same fix is needed there?  Could you please take a look at the SLES12 code to see if this hunk is needed:\n\n@@ -201,6 +201,7 @@ ext4_xattr_check_names(struct ext4_xattr\n+ \n+        while (!IS_LAST_ENTRY(entry)) {\n+               if (entry->e_value_size != 0 &&\n++                  entry->e_value_inum == 0 &&\n+                   (value_start + le16_to_cpu(entry->e_value_offs) <\n+                    (void *)e + sizeof(__u32) ||\n+                    value_start + le16_to_cpu(entry->e_value_offs) +",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
